  "texts": [
    "It can only provide demonstrations of gestures referring to given text sentences, without the function to search the meaning of a certain sequence of gestures.",
    "This limitation creates a oneway communication barrier that hinders users from translating unknown sign language gestures into text, thus falling short in their capabilities.",
    "Furthermore, the HandTalk App necessitates users to have proficiency in spoken language, which evidently poses a barrier for children who are still in the early stages of language acquisition.",
    "Some apps have addressed the latter issue by incorporating picture annotations (e.g., Pocket Signfoot_4 and ASL-Kids 9), but they similarly only manage to translate text into sign language, without the capability to translate sign language back into text or images.",
    "Proposed inclusion-aware Auslan solution System designTo support communication in families with PODCs and CODAs, our APP is centered around two pivotal functions: communication and education."
  ],
